## API Reference

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `options` | `MenuBarOption[]` | Yes | Buttons rendered in the toolbar. |
| `isActive` | `number \| boolean \| string \| undefined` | Yes | Active option value. Compared against an option id or index. |
| `optionIds` | `boolean` | No | When true, compares `isActive` to each option's `id`; otherwise compares to the option index. |
| `class` | `string` | No | Additional classes. |

MenuBar also accepts Bits UI Toolbar root props.

### `MenuBarOption`

| Property | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `icon` | `Snippet` | Yes | Icon snippet rendered inside the button. |
| `id` | `number \| string` | No | Stable option id, used for keyed rendering and active matching when `optionIds` is true. |
| `onSelect` | `() => void` | Yes | Called when the option is selected. |
| `tooltip` | `string` | Yes | Tooltip text and accessible label for the button. |

## Accessibility

MenuBar uses Bits UI's Toolbar primitive. Each option button receives an `aria-label` from `tooltip` and an `aria-pressed` state based on `isActive`.
